        <h4>Joe Turner </h4>
        <h5>Nulato</h5>
        <h6>March 3</h6>
        <q>No snow, driving on a snowmachine from Kaltag to Unalakleet. Creeks running open with open water. Low snow and warm temps meant the snowmachine kept overheating, and I had to make many stops.</q>
        <p>This change affects hunting and village travel. I first started noticing this change in 2013. I observe this change seasonally. It has a strong effect on safety.</p>
